Creating a markdown cell introducing arithmetic expression examples:                                                .  An expression in Python is a combination of operators and operands.                                               .  An example of expression can be : x = x + 1 0 x = x + 10 x=x+10.                                                     In this expression, the first 1 0 10 10 is added to the variable x.                                                  After the addition is performed, the result is assigned to the variable x.
